#Text=West Bridgewater
#Text=West Bridgewater is in the South Shore region of Massachusetts .
#Text=Understand
#Text=West
#Text=Bridgewater , also known as " WB"is a small rural town within Plymouth County and was first established in 1651 and later seceded from Bridgewater in 1822 where it became its own province .
#Text=In the late 19th century , West Bridgewater was a small farming community .
#Text=Today there still exists many fields , corn fields , and a couple farms .
#Text=Many current residents choose to live in West Bridgewater for couple of reasons .
#Text=For example the public school system remains one of the only institutions that has around 99 % of its students pass the " MCAS " test each year .
#Text=West Bridgewater is also located about 25 minutes south of Boston and provides an easy commute to work for many of its residents .
#Text=The town has a total area of 15.8 sq. miles and borders neighboring such as Brockton to the north , Bridgewater to the south , East Bridgewater to the east , and Easton to the west .
#Text=West Bridgewater is located on the historic Hockomock Swamp and the Town River passes through the southern portion of town .
#Text=Get in
#Text=By Air ,
#Text=Logan International Airport located in Boston , MA or T.F. Green Airport located in Warwick , RI .
#Text=Logan International Airport is about 45 minutes north of West Bridgewater and T.F. Green Airport is an hour drive to the south .
#Text=By Train ,
#Text=Mass Bay Transit Authority ( MBTA ) which is a commuter rail service that makes 3 stops near West Bridgewater .
#Text=1 .
#Text=Brockton 2 . Campello
#Text=3 .
#Text=Bridgewater .
#Text=From Boston to Campello it takes close to 50 minutes one way .
#Text=By Car ,
#Text=Take Route 24 South if you are driving from the north .
#Text=Take Route 24 North if you are driving from the south .
#Text=Exit 16A .
#Text=About a 30 minute drive from Boston .
#Text=By Water ,
#Text=Canoe or kayak the town river which begins in Taunton MA , and ends in West Bridgewater , MA at the War Memorial Park .
#Text=Takes about 15 hours .
#Text=Get around
#Text=The best way to navigate around West Bridgewater would be by car .
#Text=Since the town is so small walking or biking are reasonable options as well .
#Text=See
#Text=Riverbend Country Club , 250 East Center St. , West Bridgewater , MA 02379 ( Route 24 , Exit 16A ( 106 east ) 2.5 miles on your right . ) , ☏ +1508 580-3673 .
#Text=Riverbend Country Club is West Bridgewater 's premier golf course .
#Text=Specials include all you can play after 5pm on week nights .
#Text=It is an 18 hole course which plays narrow on the front 9 , but opens up on the back .
#Text=Weekday 37$ .
#Text=Do
#Text=New England Patriots .
#Text=Located a quick 20 minutes from West Bridgewater is Foxborough , MA which is home to the New England Patriots .
#Text=Commonly referred to as simply the “ Pats ” , the New England Patriots are a professional American football team followed by most of New England .
#Text=They play their home games at Gillette Stadium and are part of the AFC East Conference .

#Text=Between 2001 and 2005 the Patriots became the second team in NFL history to with three Super Bowls in four years ( XXXVI , XXXVIII , and XXXIX ) and the eighth team to win consecutive Super Bowls .
#Text=The Patriots were however defeated by the New York Giants in 2007 after posting a record setting undefeated season and win streak of 18 consecutive games .
#Text=Coach Bill Belichick and Tom Brady are local superstars and icons in Massachusetts .
#Text=Patriot Place , Two Patriot Place , Foxborough , MA 02035
#Text=( From Boston : Interstate 93 South ( S.E. Expressway ) to Interstate 95 South ; Take Interstate 95 South to Exit 9 ( Wrentham ) onto Route 1 South .
#Text=Follow Route 1 South approximately 3 miles to Patriot Place ( on the left ) . ) .
#Text=Adjacent to Gillette Stadium , Patriot Place features more than 1.3 million square feet of shopping , dining , and entertainment .
#Text=You will find major fashion retailers , live and interactive entertainment , eateries , a four-star hotel and state of the art theatre .
#Text=There is something for everyone at Patriot Place , a once in a lifetime experience every day .
#Text=Patriot Place
#Text=Hours of operation:9-11pm. Patriot Place is also a highly visited location on the South Shore .
#Text=From the CBS Sports Lounge to Bass Pro Shops , an afternoon in Foxborough does n't have to end after the Patriots game is finished .
#Text=Buy
#Text=Westgate Mall , 200 Westgate Drive
#Text=Mon - Sat : 10am-9pm , Sun : 12pm-6pm .
#Text=Westgate Mall in nearby Brockton , MA is the closest location to West Bridgewater for your shopping needs .
#Text=It is only 10 minutes away and is easy access off of route 24 north .
#Text=Main stores : Best Buy , Macy 's , Dick 's Sporting Goods , Foot Action , Finishline , Lids , American Eagle , Pac Sun , and Gamestop .
#Text=Eat
#Text=Cape Cod Cafe Pizza , 979 Main Street
#Text=Brockton , MA 02301A ( On Main Street Brockton ) , ☏ +1508 583-9420 .
#Text=11am - 10pm .
#Text=This Greek Style Restaurant has been serving gourmet pizzas since 1939 .
#Text=It is located about 3 miles north of West Bridgewater center .
#Text=Cape Cod Cafe offers a large variety of options on its menu ; all products are made fresh daily and contain nothing artificial .
#Text=You cannot go wrong with one of their famous Greek salads or weekly specials .
#Text=For example the lobster roll which is served every Friday .
#Text=Emma 's Pub and Pizza , 1420 Pleasant Street
#Text=Bridgewater , MA 02120 ( On Route 104 ) , ☏ +1508 697-8815 .
#Text=11am - 10pm .
#Text=Emma 's is your ultimate happy hour stop after a long day at work .
#Text=Drink specials coupled with a large menu of reasonably priced appetizers and entrees keep Emma 's busy Monday through Friday .
#Text=There is a spacious outdoor deck , 40 seat bar , and large dining area .
#Text=There most popular item is the 99 cent cheese pizza which is served every Wednesday from 8:30 to 10:30pm .
#Text=The atmosphere Emma 's provides is suitable for all .
#Text=Mcguire 's Bar and Grille , 503 Foundry Street
#Text=Easton , MA ( On Route 106 ) , ☏ +1508 230-8888 .
#Text=11am - 1am .
#Text=Maguire 's Bar and Grill is Easton Massachusetts ' oldest independently owned and continually operated restaurant and bar .
#Text=They offer great food and drink , at a reasonable price in a comfortable atmosphere .
#Text=Daily specials can range anywhere from yankee potroast to baked stuffed shrimp .
#Text=This establishement is also phantom gourmet approved .
#Text=Daybreak Family Restaurant , 337 W Center St West Bridgewater , MA 02379 , ☏ +1508 583-5341 .
#Text=5am - 2pm .
#Text=Daybreak Family Restaurant is a popular weekend spot for a fast delicious breakfast .
#Text=Breakfast is served all day and there is a wide range of items to choose from .
#Text=The most popular choices include eggs benedict and breakfast sandwiches .
#Text=Although the restaurant is pretty small , they keep customers moving in and out so the waiting time is usually under 15 minutes .
#Text=Asack 's Turkey Farm and Dairy Bar , 235 N Main Street West Bridgewater , MA 02379 , ☏ +1508 580-7711 .
#Text=11am - 9pm .
#Text=Asack 's Turkey Farm delivers the best and freshest turkey products .
#Text=You can walk out with a turkey pocket , turkey pot pie or turkey hot dog .
#Text=The dairy bar is open year round and the portions are generous .
#Text=It is a great place to grab a cold treat on a hot summer night .
#Text=The Charlie Horse , 647 Old West Center Street .
#Text=This is a casual bar-and-grill style restaurant whose menu features burgers , chicken dishes , salads , and fried seafood options .
#Text=Prices range from app .
#Text=$ 3 for appetizers to app .
#Text=$ 16 for some dishes .
#Text=The Charlie Horse also features an arcade game room , billiard tables , and central bar outfitted with televisions for watching sporting events .
